    "causal_summary": "The Spec-Kit Memory MCP index is partly cold: a measurable fraction of indexed rows are un-enriched / un-embedded, and the FTS/vector consistency state is degraded. Until that coverage is restored, **no recall, calibration, or cold-tier number can be trusted** — a benchmark run against a quarter-dark index silently measures the wrong corpus and believes the result. The 028 retrieval-evaluation campaign (child `008-retrieval-evaluation`) named this **the hard precondition for every recall-affecting candidate**: \"Reindex is gate-zero\" (`synthesis/08-retrieval-evaluation-findings.md` §\"How to read each entry\"; \"Honest caveats\"). The eval harness itself only checks ground-truth ID parenthood/presence (`assertGroundTruthAlignment`, `ablation-framework.ts:314`), not embedding coverage — so it cannot today refuse to run against a cold index.",
